[assistant] Fixed the failing `ClassPoolTest` setup.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - The two `toClass(...)` tests used `new ClassPool(false)`, which does not include the default/system class path, so Javassist could not resolve `java.lang.Object` while generating bytecode.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Updated both tests to use `new ClassPool(true)` so the pool has the default system path available.
[assistant] 
